Salix lasiolepis and Salix laevigata stand on either bank of southern facing slope. A nearby meandering stream runs through stand. The stream also forms islands where willow and Cephalanthus occidentalis occur. Stand has a fairly open overstory and low shrub density in the overstory and herbs dominate in the understory. Riparian corridor is ~20m wide. Stream channelizes in places with high/steep banks. Associated taxa Salix laevigata. 4098927 UTMN, 269342 UTME (NAD 83 GPS, 11 Zone; 37.8225, -119.592394). Elev 268 m.
